# MCP and plugin routing

Development is **100% in Cursor**. Prefer **checked-in `scripts/*.sh`** for build/run/test
(the deterministic local loop). Use MCPs to augment — not replace — those scripts.

## Enabled MCP servers (current)

| Server ID | Name | Use for |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `user-xcodebuildmcp` | xcodebuildmcp | Apple platform build/test/run via MCP tools (see scope below) |
| `user-context7` | context7 | Library/SDK/CLI docs (`resolve-library-id` → `query-docs`) |
| `plugin-chrome-devtools-mcp-chrome-devtools` | chrome-devtools | Website verification (`navigate_page`, `take_snapshot`, `take_screenshot`, …) |
| `cursor-ide-browser` | cursor-ide-browser | In-IDE browser tab (`browser_navigate`, `browser_snapshot`, …) |
| `plugin-huggingface-skills-huggingface-skills` | huggingface-skills | Hub model/dataset/paper lookup (`hub_repo_search`, `hub_repo_details`, …) |
| `cursor-app-control` | cursor-app-control | Cursor IDE control (`open_resource`, `move_agent_to_root`, `rename_chat`, …) |
| `peekaboo` | peekaboo | **User-global** macOS desktop automation (`see`, `image`, `click`, `type`, `hotkey`, …) — exploratory QA only |
| `mirroir` | mirroir | **User-global** iPhone Mirroring drive (`describe_screen`, `tap`, `swipe`, …) — exploratory QA on real device. French macOS needs `~/.mirroir-mcp/settings.json` → `mirroringProcessName: "Recopie de l'iPhone"` (pilot log §5) |
| `user-axiom` | axiom | Apple-platform skills, auditors, and CLI wrappers (`axiom_read_skill`, `axiom_get_agent`, `axiom_xcsym_*`, …). Config key **`axiom`** in `~/.cursor/mcp.json`; invoke as **`user-axiom`** in `CallMcpTool`. Launch: `npx -y axiom-mcp` ([install docs](https://charleswiltgen.github.io/Axiom/start/mcp-install)). |

Configured in **`~/.cursor/mcp.json`** (not committed). Peekaboo and mirroir launch via
`$HOME/.cursor/bin/mcp_stdio_wrapper.sh` (Cursor spawn env fix). Setup:
[`docs/reference/computer-use-mcp-alternatives-cursor.md`](mdc:docs/reference/computer-use-mcp-alternatives-cursor.md),
[`docs/reference/ios-agent-ui-tour.md`](mdc:docs/reference/ios-agent-ui-tour.md).

Invoke MCP tools with **`CallMcpTool`** (read each tool's JSON descriptor under the MCP
filesystem first). Use the **Shell** tool for terminal commands — not a separate Bash tool.

## XcodeBuildMCP (`user-xcodebuildmcp`)

Read the **`xcodebuildmcp`** skill (`SKILL.md`) before first use.

**Enabled workflows** (see repo [`.xcodebuildmcp/config.yaml`](mdc:.xcodebuildmcp/config.yaml)):
`macos`, `device`, `debugging`, `project-discovery`.
Reload the MCP server after editing that file (Cursor → Settings → MCP → xcodebuildmcp → Restart).

Tools include `session_show_defaults`, `session_use_defaults_profile`, `build_macos`,
`build_run_macos`, `test_macos`, `test_device`, `list_devices`, etc.

**Session discipline (required):**

1. Call `session_show_defaults` before the first build/run/test in a session.
2. Switch profiles with `session_use_defaults_profile`: `macos` (`QwenVoice`),
   `ios-device` (set `deviceId` via `session_set_defaults`).
3. Use `discover_projs` only when defaults are missing or wrong — never speculatively.

**Vocello routing:**

- **macOS app (`QwenVoice` scheme):** `./scripts/build.sh` remains primary; MCP
  `build_run_macos` / `test_macos` are OK for quick checks (`session_use_defaults_profile: macos`).
- **iOS (`VocelloiOS`):** prefer `scripts/ios_device.sh` on a paired iPhone for all UI tests
  and real-engine work. MCP `device` tools are optional helpers (profile `ios-device` + runtime
  `deviceId`). **Never** use Simulator or simulator UI tools for iOS. Post-run triage playbook:
  [`ios-device-testing.md` § Agent + MCP workflow](mdc:docs/reference/ios-device-testing.md#agent--mcp-workflow)
  (`test-runner` on `build/ios/Logs/Test/*.xcresult`; `check_ios_ui_bench.py` on
  `build/ios-diagnostics/`; `axiom_xcprof_analyze` on `bench-ui --profile` traces).

## Context7 (`user-context7`)

For GRDB, SwiftHuggingFace, React, Vite, and any non-Apple library docs — even when you
think you know the API. Do **not** use for refactoring, business logic, or general CS.

Steps: `resolve-library-id` → pick best `/org/project` match → `query-docs` with the full
question. User rule: [`.cursor/rules/context7.mdc`](mdc:.cursor/rules/context7.mdc) (if
present at user level, same policy applies).

## Browser verification (website)

For `website/`: read `website/PRODUCT.md` + `website/DESIGN.md`, then either:

- **`chrome-devtools`** MCP — full DevTools (network, performance, Lighthouse), or
- **`cursor-ide-browser`** MCP — lightweight in-IDE tab automation.

Run `npm --prefix website run dev|preview` via Shell first.

## Hugging Face (`plugin-huggingface-skills-huggingface-skills`)

For model revision lookup, dataset metadata, and hub search. The **`hf` CLI** and Hugging
Face skills remain valid for downloads and local model management.

## Cursor app control (`cursor-app-control`)

Use sparingly: `open_resource` to reveal files/terminals/URLs in Glass, `rename_chat` for
conversation titles, `move_agent_to_root` after worktree switches. Do **not** use for
build/test automation.

## Axiom MCP (`axiom` / `user-axiom`)

Apple-platform skills, auditors, and bundled CLI wrappers via **`user-axiom`** (`CallMcpTool`).
Config key in `~/.cursor/mcp.json` is **`axiom`** (per [Axiom MCP install](https://charleswiltgen.github.io/Axiom/start/mcp-install)).

**Discovery workflow (read tool schema first):**

1. `axiom_get_catalog` or `axiom_search_skills` — browse / find skills
2. `axiom_read_skill` — load skill content (prefer `sections` filter for token efficiency)
3. `axiom_get_agent` — fetch auditor/agent instructions, then follow in-session or via Task
   `generalPurpose` when scope is large

**Auditors:** `axiom_get_agent` with agent names such as `concurrency-auditor`,
`memory-auditor`, `swiftui-architecture-auditor`, `security-privacy-scanner`,
`accessibility-auditor`, `screenshot-validator`, `crash-analyzer`, `build-fixer`,
`test-runner`, `performance-profiler`.

**Artifact analysis (prefer MCP tools over raw shell):**

| Need | MCP tool |
| --- | --- |
| Crash symbolication | `axiom_xcsym_crash`, `axiom_xcsym_triage` |
| Profile analysis | `axiom_xcprof_analyze`, `axiom_xcprof_compare` |
| Console logs | `axiom_xclog_attach`, `axiom_xclog_show` |

**Do not** drive app UI through Axiom `xcui` / `simulator-tester` for iOS — use
deterministic XCUITest + `scripts/ios_device.sh`.

## UI review baselines (vision diff)

After `scripts/macos_test.sh review` or `scripts/ios_device.sh review`, compare captures
vs `docs/*-review-baselines/` using `axiom_get_agent` agent=`screenshot-validator` or a
manual visual pass. The retired `zai-mcp-server` `ui_diff_check` tool is no longer available.

## Retired / off-limits

- Agent/computer-use **shell** driving (`uitest.sh`, mirror coordinate hacks in `ios_device.sh`) — gone; see [`testing-runbook.md`](mdc:docs/reference/testing-runbook.md).
- **User-global exploratory MCP** (Jul 2026 pilot): **`peekaboo`** (macOS Vocello.app) and **`mirroir`** (iPhone Mirroring on paired device) in `~/.cursor/mcp.json` — **exploratory QA only**; pre-merge gates remain `macos_test.sh gate` / `ios_device.sh gate`. Do not use mirroir for CI; do not resurrect mirror clicks in shell scripts.
- **Axiom Cursor plugin** — removed; superseded by Axiom MCP (`axiom` / `user-axiom`). Do not
  use `/axiom:*` slash commands, plugin skill paths, or plugin `bin/` routing.
- **`plugin-xcodebuildmcp-sentry`** — removed; use `user-xcodebuildmcp`.
- iOS Simulator for any Vocello test or agent workflow — off-limits (§7 in root [`AGENTS.md`](mdc:AGENTS.md)).
